<TITLE> Govt okays 3 new medical colleges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 14(bdnews24.com)-The government has accorded permission for set up of three new private medical colleges, health minister AFM Ruhul Huq told parliament on Sunday. No appointments have been made yet for the new medical colleges in Noakhali, Cox's Bazar and Pabna, he added. The government is also going to appoint 4,133 doctors on an ad-hoc basis, and fill up vacant posts of assistant civil surgeons through the Public Service Commission, the minister said in reply to a question from HM Golam Reza MP of Satkhira. Replying to another question from ABM Ashrafuddin Nizam of Lakhipur, Huq said there were 17 government medical colleges across the country. Some 20,000 students study in private medical colleges, the minister said in reply to a query by Benazir Ahmed MP from Dhaka. bdnew
